channel.title: Tor Bootstrap Issue
channel.description:
I tried to install Tor Browser and got this message: ERROR: Tor not fully bootstrapped. Possible reasons: - no internet connectivity Please check: Start menu -> System -> systemcheck or in Terminal: systemcheck or in Terminal with debugging: systemcheck -v Run systemcheck on Whonix-Gateway as well. If systemcheck reports no problems with internet activity and downloading Tor Browser still fails, please report a bug!
I then ran the command and: user@host:~$ systemcheck -v [INFO] [systemcheck] | Whonix-Workstation | Tue 31 Aug 2021 01:27:39 PM UTC [INFO] [systemcheck] Check sudo Result: OK [INFO] [systemcheck] Whonix build version: 15.0.1.9.3 [INFO] [systemcheck] whonix-workstation-packages-dependencies-cli: 21.5-1 [INFO] [systemcheck] derivative_major_release_version /etc/whonix_version: 15 [INFO] [systemcheck] Whonix Support Status of this Major Version: Ok. If you know what you are doing, feel free to disable this check. item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
That is, if whonixcheck on Whonix-Gateway also shows Tor isn’t connected and none of the advice by whonixcheck helps to resolve the issue.

Read full topic

item.title: Tor Bootstrap Issue
item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
37874938:

Maybe I need a VPN inside Whonix in order to install Tor Browser?

No. Whonix-Gateway uses host system default network by default.

It’s unrelated, optional and would only add confusion at this stage: Combining Tunnels with Tor

37874938:

If so how would I do that as there is no other working browser?

Before attempting to make Tor Browser work inside Whonix-Workstation, first Tor inside Whonix-Gateway needs to be made to work.

Please try Tor Generic Bug Reproduction.

Read full topic

Maybe I need a VPN inside Whonix in order to install Tor Browser? If so how would I do that as there is no other working browser?

item.title: Tor Bootstrap Issue
item.description:
I tried to install Tor Browser and got this message:
ERROR: Tor not fully bootstrapped.
Possible reasons:

  • no internet connectivity
    Please check:
    Start menu → System → systemcheck
    or in Terminal: systemcheck
    or in Terminal with debugging: systemcheck -v
    Run systemcheck on Whonix-Gateway as well.
    If systemcheck reports no problems with internet activity and downloading Tor Browser still fails, please report a bug!
